[I watched the New York City press conference from Bellevue hospital on CNN TV tonight. The speakers, who included CDC Director Tom Frieden by telephone link from Atlanta, emphasized that he only developed fever after a 3-mile jog this morning, 23 Oct 2014. Since Ebola is not airborne and only spread by contact with the body fluids of a patient with symptoms, so that there is no need for people to be alarmed who visited the restaurant or bowling alley that he went to yesterday, or traveled on the city taxi or subway he traveled on yesterday. - Mod.JW

